Manchester City continue to await their fate after being charged with numerous financial breaches by the Premier League. If found guilty, the reigning champions face possible punishments which could include points deductions or even expulsion from the top flight. The Premier League made the unprecedented statement on Monday that City had been charged with a list of alleged offences. The matter has been referred to an independent commission, who will come to a conclusion on the matter. No timeframe has been put on when City could receive their punishments if a guilty verdict is reached. But there are fears at City that retrospective action could be taken and they could be stripped of some previously won silverware. The story is developing all the time and will continue to rumble on, so follow Express Sport's live blog below for the latest updates and news... 